Appendix F: Self‑Attention Parameterisation – Properties

Definition F.1 (Attention Matrix).
For a set of capsules with feature matrix \mathbf{X} \in \mathbb{R}^{N \times d},

\mathbf{A} = \text{softmax}\left( \frac{\mathbf{X}\mathbf{X}^\top}{\sqrt{d}} \right),
\]  

where softmax is applied row‑wise.

Lemma F.1 (Skew‑Symmetrisation).
\mathbf{J} = \mathbf{A} - \mathbf{A}^\top is skew‑symmetric by construction.

Lemma F.2 (Positive Definiteness of \mathbf{R}).
\mathbf{R} = \text{Softplus}(\mathbf{A}) where \text{Softplus}(x) = \log(1+e^x) applied element‑wise yields a matrix with strictly positive diagonal entries. Hence \mathbf{R} \succ 0 (positive definite).

Lemma F.3 (Lipschitz Continuity).
The mapping \mathbf{X} \mapsto \mathbf{A} is Lipschitz on bounded sets because softmax and the quadratic form are Lipschitz.

