Appendix G: Two‑Timescale Convergence – Detailed Proof

Theorem G.1 (Tracking Error Bound).
Under Assumptions 4.1, the tracking error satisfies

\limsup_{t \to \infty} \|\mathbf{c}^{(t)} - \mathbf{c}^*(\mathbf{W}^{(k(t))})\| \le \frac{M\eta B G}{1-\rho}.

Proof. Within a plasticity block (index k), after t routing iterations,

e^{(k,t)} \le \rho^t e^{(k,0)}.
\]  

The initial error of the next block is

e^{(k+1,0)} \le e^{(k,T)} + \|\mathbf{c}^*(\mathbf{W}^{(k+1)}) - \mathbf{c}^*(\mathbf{W}^{(k)})\|,
\]  

where T is the number of routing iterations per block. The second term is bounded by M\|\mathbf{W}^{(k+1)}-\mathbf{W}^{(k)}\| \le M\eta B G. If we run enough routing iterations so that \rho^T e^{(k,0)} \le \epsilon_0, then the recurrence gives

e^{(k+1,0)} \le \epsilon_0 + M\eta B G.
\]  

The steady‑state error satisfies e_\infty = \rho^T e_\infty + M\eta B G, so

e_\infty = \frac{M\eta B G}{1-\rho^T}.
\]  

Choosing T large enough makes \rho^T negligible, yielding the bound. ∎

