Appendix I: Homeostatic Scaling – Convergence

Definition I.1 (Scaling Map).
For capsule j, let E_j = \sum_i \|\mathbf{W}_{ij}\mathbf{u}_i\|. The scaling factor is \alpha = T / (E_j + \varepsilon). Updated weights: \mathbf{W}_{ij}' = \alpha \mathbf{W}_{ij}.

Lemma I.1 (Fixed Point).
The unique fixed point satisfies E_j = T for all j. Under the scaling map, E_j converges geometrically to T if \mathbf{u}_i are bounded away from zero.

Proof. After scaling, the new total input is E_j' = \alpha E_j = T E_j/(E_j+\varepsilon). This is a contraction on (0,\infty) with fixed point T. ∎

