Appendix J: Discretisation for Causal Emergence – Bias Analysis

Lemma J.1 (Quantisation Bias).
Let \mathbf{u} be a continuous capsule output with distribution P. After vector quantisation to n codebooks, the resulting Markov chain transition probabilities T^{(n)} satisfy

\|T^{(n)} - T^{(\infty)}\|_1 \le \frac{C}{\sqrt{n}} + O(\text{distortion}),
\]  

where T^{(\infty)} is the limiting transition kernel as n \to \infty (if it exists). This follows from standard vector quantisation theory (e.g., consistency of k‑means).

Theorem J.1 (Consistency of CP under Refinement).
If the true underlying process is a continuous‑state Markov chain with smooth transition kernel, then as n \to \infty and N \to \infty (with n growing slower than N), \widehat{\mathrm{CP}} \to \mathrm{CP}^*, the causal power of the continuous system.

Proof. Combine the quantisation bias decay with the estimation consistency (Theorem 6.1) and choose n \sim N^{1/3} to balance bias and variance. ∎

