Appendix K: Path‑Based Hierarchical Apportionment – Invariance

Definition K.1 (Coarse‑graining Equivalence).
Two coarse‑grainings \gamma and \gamma' are equivalent if there exists a bijection \phi on macro‑states such that \gamma' = \phi \circ \gamma.

Lemma K.1 (Invariance of CP).
If \gamma and \gamma' are equivalent, then \mathrm{CP}(S_\gamma) = \mathrm{CP}(S_{\gamma'}).

Proof. A bijection on state labels does not change entropy or transition probabilities up to permutation, so determinism and specificity are invariant. ∎

Lemma K.2 (Unique Contribution Non‑negativity).
\mathrm{unique}_k \ge 0 by definition, and \mathrm{unique}_k = 0 if and only if \mathrm{CP}(S_k) \le \mathrm{CP}(S_{k-1}).

